SELECT
        c.customerID,
        c.customerName,
        c.contact,
        COUNT(o.orderID) as order_count,
        CASE
            WHEN COUNT(o.orderID) > 0 THEN TRUE
            ELSE FALSE
        END AS has_orders
    FROM demo_etl.customers c
    LEFT JOIN demo_etl.orders o ON c.customerID = o.customerID
    GROUP BY c.customerID, c.customerName, c.contact
    ORDER BY order_count DESC

SELECT
        p.productName,
        COUNT(s.OrderID) as total_sales,
        SUM(s.Quantity) as total_quantity,
        ROUND(AVG(s.Quantity), 2) as avg_quantity_per_sale
    FROM demo_etl.products p
    LEFT JOIN demo_etl.sales s ON p.productID = s.productID
    GROUP BY p.productName
    ORDER BY total_sales DESC
